cafes.name: Mew Haven Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 904 Whalley Ave, New Haven, CT 06515, USA

text.text: We visited Mew Heaven Cat Cafe on Sunday, and it was such a delightful experience! Booking our tickets ahead of time online was super easy and convenient. Once we arrived, we enjoyed some delicious coffee and tea while spending time with the adorable cats. The space is cozy, and the staff, especially Angela, the owner, was super friendly and welcoming. She really made our visit even more special. It‚Äôs the perfect place to relax and enjoy some time with furry friends. We had a great time and will definitely be back! Highly recommend for any cat lover!

This was such an amazing experience! The staff was so friendly. The gift shop prices were amazing! They also have a sheet on how each cat acts. A cat climbed up on my lap for around 30-40 minutes. It is such a beautiful and simple experience. I recommend that everyone goes here at least once. My only complaints are  that it's is only around 1 hour! Lol! I would spend all day here if I was able to! Also, It was around 30 minutes away! I wish there were so many more of these across the world!!!!! Overall, this was one of the best experiences of my life! If it is so relaxing and so enjoyable. I really hope to go back again soon!!!!!

This place is amazing! My granddaughter loved loved to pet the cats and she had a great time. I had a good relaxing time as well! I had cats as long as I can remember my self, so seeing all these babies today it was an amazing experience!! We will definitely visit you again.

I smile from ear to ear every time I visit because CATS!!!  Marcie's is warm, inviting, tastefully decorated, tidy. They offer a variety of events like sip and paints, cat yoga, etc.  If you'd like to directly help their cause, book a session and spend some time with the kitties or better yet, think about fostering. Knowing that you're helping animals in need by providing a safe and loving home is such a
rewarding feeling. Thank you Marcie's for bringing such a special little place to the area!!

Such a wonderful experience, love the services that this facility provides to the otherwise forgotten about, felines.

The owner was there to welcome us and was a very humble, caring individual. Would definitely recommend going in the morning or earlier in the day since the kitties get tired near the end of the day. What a special place though, highly recommend and love the cute gift shop they have there too.

Absolutely amazing place! We love what they are doing for those sweet animals. There is a fee to enter and see the cats. However, the cafe side is always open to the public. The desserts are 10/10 and so delicious! They also offer gluten free options. My 7 and 4 year old had a blast. The owner is the sweetest and we felt so welcomed! We love what they are doing for our local community and can‚Äôt wait to go again.

cafes.name: Perk and Paws Cat Cafe
cafes.address: 100 Franklin St Suite A, Torrington, CT 06790, USA

text.text:
What a wonderful little spot!! It was a calm and clean environment. The owner was taking care of the customers himself and he was so kind and fun to chat with.

The cat area was so relaxing, cute and well-decorated. They let in just a small amount of people at a time for the cats' sake, so you do not feel overcrowded. There is plenty of space and time to visit all the kitties in the room (I believe there were 6 or 7) and there are plenty of toys to use with them. They seemed well-cared for and content. We aren't in a position to adopt sadly, but there is no pressure at all if you just want to hang with them.

The beverages were so reasonably priced that I tried both an iced coffee and a hot chocolate. Both were SO GOOD and they have a variety of flavors to add to anything.

10/10 will return!! The hour drive for me is worth it.

We went this past weekend for a visit. There were 5-6 beautiful friendly cats to visit, all available for adoption. We had some coffee and hot tea. The owners were friendly and welcoming and very passionate about their business! Highly recommend visiting! We will be back!

I brought my mom here for her birthday and we had the best time. The staff are all incredibly kind and friendly and it's a very relaxed environment. They clearly take excellent care of their cats, who are all adoptable. The kitties that were there were very playful and sweet, and had we been in the market for adopting it would have been an impossible choice. Highly recommend for a cozy afternoon or if you're beginning your cat adoption journey.

East Haddam.name: Two Wrasslin' Cats Coffee House & Cafe
East Haddam.address: 374 Town St, East Haddam, CT 06423, USA

text.text: Came for the coffee and croissant, stayed for the cats üòÅ. Great spot to go out for a drive. The outdoor seating looks like it would be amazing during the spring and summertime. There's great seating outside next to the creek. Inside, what can be said, if you ever thought of a cat themed decoration, they have it. The coffee tasted great, and they offer a good choice of sandwiches.

This was a super cool cafe to stop in on our day of adventure. The customer service was phenomenal and everyone was super chill. Coffee was very good, my wrap was good, and my girlfriend very much enjoyed her bagel sandwich. Cat themed and eccentric design alone was worth checking out, you can also hangout with the 6 residence cats in their playroom for a small donation.

An adorable cat cafe where you can hang with cats, drink cappuccino, and talk with the very kind owner. Great spot to just hang out in and you can either look through the glass window at the cats or play with them yourself, but either way, adorable.

5 stars!!!!
